            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
               <listApp>
                   <app><note>text as per Sofia 2018</note></app>
              </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>(tomb) of Athanippos</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#JP">
                <p>The epitaph consists of a single name in the genitive, as with the majority of the epitaphs attested from this necropolis. The name <ref target="http://www.lgpn.ox.ac.uk/name/%E1%BC%88%CE%B8%CE%AC%CE%BD%CE%B9%CF%80%CF%80%CE%BF%CF%82">Ἀθάνιππος</ref> is not a common one, with only one other known (probably) Sicilian instance (IG II/III (2nd edn) 10293: Ἕρμων | Ἀθανίππου | Σικελὸς | ἀπὸ Τυνδαρίδος, a funerary inscription from Athens of the imperial period.</p>
            </div>
